  "description": [
    "Till COURIERJOURNAL LOUISVILLE TUESDAY MORNING OCTOBER 30 1900 LEADING GiTiLiuiAmerican Law yer Strong For Bryan JUDGE RODERICK ROMBAUER LIFELONG BEPUBLICAN OF ST LOUIS ISSUES STATEMENT OPPOSED TO IMPERIALISM Gives Reasons At Length Tor Oppos ing ReElection of McKinley ALWAYS SOUND MONEY MAN St Louis Oct 29 Judge Roderick F Rombauer the most distinguished GermanAmerican lawyer in this city and a lifelong Republican has given to the St Louis Republic a statement explain ing why he will vote for Bryan for President Judge Rombauer served two terms on the Circuit Court bench and one term in the Court of Apepals cf which he was Presiding Judge for ten years He Is a man of great popularity and has always led his ticket thousands of votes His statement is as follows A few weeks ago in a special dispatch to the Republic from Washington my name was mentioned among the names of several hundred Republicans more or less prominent who at the approaching elec tion intended to cast their votes for Will iam J Bryan Ever since I have been harassed by personal and political friends to give them an explanation of the rea sons for this supposed change in my po"
